body:
@navina 
We decided to disable integration tests by default in local builds and run them by default in jenkins. 

If acceptable, please add property `includeSamzaTest ` to jenkins gradle cmd(I don't have edit permissions in jenkins).

@navina 
Default value for timeouts are very high (order of 30s) [I don't have complete context behind the decision].
Let's revisit it when there're production problems[Highly likely to happen].

@prateekm 
Updated relevant docs.

Please take a look.

@jmakes 
`I assume nothing's changed for low level api. It's still config driven for all serdes, right?`
Yeah, should not affect low level api.

@dnishimura Looking better, but if we really want to put this issue to rest, it looks like we'll need a similar change in JavaSystemConfig.java

*sigh* we really shouldn't have both and the Samza project has vowed to use Java for everything new. But it looks like at least for now there's some duplication in this area.

Apologies for the trouble, but would you mind either making the analogous change in JavaSystemConfig or doing a little refactoring so there's only one method to fetch the systemFactory?

@sborya take a look!

Also, because of the PR number, I gotta say: 
"THIS.... IS.... SPARTA!!!!"

@nickpan47 @jmakes : Can you guys please take a look at this patch? 

@xiliu : Once this PR is committed, if you need to add anything from your multi-stage batch PRs to the release/upgrade notes, please add them. Thanks! 

PS: Let's start this process from 0.14.0. Hence, this patch is targeted at 0.14.0 branch.
